id: pm-hw6z
title: Handle concurrent project package installs without EEXIST
description: "Live Sentry issue PM-CLI-X showed concurrent pm install npm:pm-changelog --project can race on the extension destination directory and fail with EEXIST mkdir. Make package/extension install robust under concurrent same-target installs without changing pm-changelog."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: extensions,install,robustness,sentry
created_at: "2026-05-24T13:13:42.077Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-24T13:36:42.402Z"
author: codex-changelog-ci
acceptance_criteria: Concurrent installs of the same project extension do not surface raw EEXIST; package doctor remains clean; regression coverage proves the race handling.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Concurrent extension/package installs now serialize per destination and no longer surface raw EEXIST/ENOTEMPTY copy races.
expected_result: "Same-target project extension installs should either both succeed or return a controlled lock timeout, while pm-changelog remains active and doctor-clean."
actual_result: Two simultaneous pm-changelog installs both succeeded; doctor reported status ok; changelog check stayed unchanged; regression tests passed.
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-24T13:20:40.158Z",codex-changelog-ci,"Evidence: reproduced Sentry PM-CLI-X as a concurrent same-target pm install race. Added serialized extension install lock around destination copy + managed-state update, retained copy retry for transient filesystem races, verified two simultaneous node dist/cli.js install npm:pm-changelog --project processes both exit 0, package doctor is clean, pnpm changelog:pm:check passed, static quality passed, focused extension unit tests passed, focused release automation/readiness tests passed."
  "2026-05-24T13:36:42.402Z",codex-changelog-ci,"Review response: accepted CodeRabbit nitpick and removed the unreachable throw after copy retry loop; focused extension/release tests still pass."
